To measure molecular diversity, we adopted the metric proposed by Solow and Polasky in 1994 to estimate the diversity of a biological population in an eco-system [35]. It has been shown to be an effective method to measure the diversity of drug molecules [36]. The formula to calculate diversity was redefined to normalize the range of values from [1, m] to (0, m] as follows:IA=1Ae⊺F(s)-1e\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
